<p class="head"><span style="text-decoration:underline;">Theology</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">The Chipweans have always been, and are even at this day in a state of the darkest superstition and ignorance; which is somewhat singular, considering the long and uninterrupted intercourse they have had with the Europeans; as it <span class="AddHand-author">might</span> reasonably <span class="AddHand-author">be</span> expected that they would have become more enlightened: &#8211; but so far to the contrary; that they seem to be more tenacious of their doctrines, than they are said to have entertained at a more remote period; which may arise from a twofold cause; viz. the licentious manners of the Europeans &#8211; and litterly the courtious attention which is shown to them, must no doubt flatter their pride, as they have a firm belief that they are superior in knowledge to the white people.  Notwithstanding they believe that there exists a Supreme Being, whose power can bring down Death, and Famine, upon them; Yet they cannot</p>

